dct_title_s: The Irish or St. George’s Channel [sheet 3]
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings. Oriented with north to the right. Includes ill., notes and views. In margin: Chart no. 14. Insets: Firth of Clyde -- Douglas Bay -- Belfast Lough -- Maryport -- North Rocks -- Lough Strangford -- Carlingford Lough -- Lough Foyle -- Manchester ship canal -- Milford Haven -- Lundy Island -- Tuskar Rocks -- Holyhead Bay. Historic Maps copy has stamp: Corrected to 1896. James Imray & Son, 89, Minories, London. Historic Maps copy has label on verso: Chart no. 14. Irish Channel. Historic maps has ms. annotations.
dct_publisher_sm: London : Published by James Imray and Son, 89 and 89a Minories, 1895.
